title: Florida woman extends Alaska vacation to search for lost cat
text:
Florida woman extends Alaska vacation to search for lost cat   12, 2015 at 11:37 am A Florida woman's love for her missing 10-pound cat is leading her to extend her vacation in Alaska. The Associated Press 
KENAI, Alaska — A Florida woman’s love for her cat is leading her to extend her vacation in Alaska. 
A 10-pound black and white male cat named Tucker disappeared after Robin Wiesneth, 50, of Miramar Beach and her husband, Charles, were involved in a fatal traffic crash Aug. 5 on the Kenai Spur Highway. 
A pickup with two people crossed the highway centerline and crashed into the Weisneths’ motorhome. Both people in the truck died. The Weisneths suffered minor injuries. 
The Peninsula Clarion, a Kenai newspaper, reports (http://bit.ly/1HGU29k) Tucker was on Robin Weisneth’s lap in a small cat bed when the crash occurred. Most Read Stories
